---
title: One-Pan Santa Fe Chicken Tacos with Monterey Jack & Cilantro Citrus Slaw
description: We firmly believe taco night should be treated like a holiday—one that should be celebrated at LEAST once a week, if not more. If you agree, you’ve got to add this Southwest version to your repertoire. Spiced ground pork and onion are piled into steamy tortillas with Monterey Jack cheese, a tangy cilantro citrus slaw, and sour cream. Taco ’bout a killer meal.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/one-pan-santa-fe-pork-tacos-76452943.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/65145a6f3cb5229806dac8d5.pdf
time required: 20 minutes
cuisine: Mexican
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/one-pan-santa-fe-chickentacos-65145a6f3cb5229806dac8d5
author: Michelle Doll Olson
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 760 kcal
  fat: 36 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 65 g
  sugar: 14 g
  protein: 44 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 1780 mg
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry produce. Halve @yellow onion{1}(peeled and finely diced). Finely chop @cilantro{1/4%oz}. Quarter @lemon{1}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add onion and a pinch of @salt{}; cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened and lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @chopped chicken breast{10%oz} and @Southwest spice blend{1%tbsp}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. TIP: If there's excess grease in your pan, carefully pour it out.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

While pork cooks, in a large #bowl{}, combine @shredded red cabbage{4%oz}, @mayonnaise{2%tbsp}, half the cilantro, juice from half the lemon (whole lemon for 4 servings), @sugar{1%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{pinch}.

Stir @Tex-Mex paste{1} into pan with pork mixture until fully coated. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove pan from heat.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with pork filling, @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}, slaw, @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, and remaining cilantro. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the side.